# HTML Table Tag Quick Sheet

* **Purpose**: Displays data in a structured grid of rows and columns.
* **Core Tag**: `<table>` wraps the entire table layout.

## Essential Child Tags
* `<tr>`: Table Row (creates a horizontal line of data).
* `<th>`: Table Header (bold, centered text for column labels).
* `<td>`: Table Data (standard cell content).

## Code Example
```html
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Role</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Alice</td>
    <td>Developer</td>
  </tr>
</table>
```
